{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 11 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:1",
      "text": "Be ye followers of me, as I also am of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:2",
      "text": "Now I praise you, brethren, that in all things you are mindful of me and keep my ordinances as I have delivered them to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:3",
      "text": "But I would have you know that the head of every man is Christ: and the head of the woman is the man: and the head of Christ is God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:4",
      "text": "Every man praying or prophesying with his head covered disgraceth his head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:5",
      "text": "But every woman praying or prophesying with her head not covered disgraceth her head: for it is all one as if she were shaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:6",
      "text": "For if a woman be not covered, let her be shorn. But if it be a shame to a woman to be shorn or made bald, let her cover her head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:7",
      "text": "The man indeed ought not to cover his head: because he is the image and glory of God. But the woman is the glory of the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:8",
      "text": "For the man is not of the woman: but the woman of the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:9",
      "text": "For the man was not created for the woman: but the woman for the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:10",
      "text": "Therefore ought the woman to have a power over her head, because of the angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:11",
      "text": "But yet neither is the man without the woman, nor the woman without the man, in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:12",
      "text": "For as the woman is of the man, so also is the man by the woman: but all things of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:13",
      "text": "You yourselves judge. Doth it become a woman to pray unto God uncovered?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:14",
      "text": "Doth not even nature itself teach you that a man indeed, if he nourish his hair, it is a shame unto him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:15",
      "text": "But if a woman nourish her hair, it is a glory to her; for her hair is given to her for a covering.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:16",
      "text": "But if any man seem to be contentious, we have no such custom, nor the Church of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:17",
      "text": "Now this I ordain: not praising you, that you come together, not for the better, but for the worse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:18",
      "text": "For first of all I hear that when you come together in the church, there are schisms among you. And in part I believe it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:19",
      "text": "For there must be also heresies: that they also, who are approved may be made manifest among you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:20",
      "text": "When you come therefore together into one place, it is not now to eat the Lord's supper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:21",
      "text": "For every one taketh before his own supper to eat. And one indeed is hungry and another is drunk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:22",
      "text": "What, have you no houses to eat and to drink in? Or despise ye the church of God and put them to shame that have not? What shall I say to you? Do I praise you? In this I praise you not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:23",
      "text": "For I have received of the Lord that which also I delivered unto you, that the Lord Jesus, the same night in which he was betrayed, took bread,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:24",
      "text": "And giving thanks, broke and said: Take ye and eat: This is my body, which shall be delivered for you. This do for the commemoration of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:25",
      "text": "In like manner also the chalice, after he had supped, saying: This chalice is the new testament in my blood. This do ye, as often as you shall drink, for the commemoration of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:26",
      "text": "For as often as you shall eat this bread and drink the chalice, you shall shew the death of the Lord, until he come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:27",
      "text": "Therefore, whosoever shall eat this bread, or drink the chalice of the Lord unworthily, shall be guilty of the body and of the blood of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:28",
      "text": "But let a man prove himself: and so let him eat of that bread and drink of the chalice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:29",
      "text": "For he that eateth and drinketh unworthily eateth and drinketh judgment to himself, not discerning the body of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:30",
      "text": "Therefore are there many infirm and weak among you: and many sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:31",
      "text": "But if we would judge ourselves, we should not be judged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:32",
      "text": "But whilst we are judged, we are chastised by the Lord, that we be not condemned with this world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:33",
      "text": "Wherefore, my brethren, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-corinthians.11.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:34",
      "text": "If any man be hungry, let him eat at home; that you come not together unto judgment. And the rest I will set in order, when I come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
